title: Complete coverage: Pen Argyl grinds its way past WIlson for first football win of the season
text:
Complete Box Score Â» 
Pen Argyl used a powerful running game and a big-play capability to post its first win of the season, 49-28, over Wilson Saturday afternoon at Alumni Stadium in Pen Argyl. 
Green Knight sophomore running back Logan Sterner ran for a school-record-tying five touchdowns while Warrior quarterback Cameron Clark threw for a school-record 349 yards.
